      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:4:38:4",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " إِنَّ عَلِيّاً ( عليه السلام ) قَضَى فِي شَحْمَةِ الْأُذُنِ ثُلُثَ دِيَةِ الْأُذُنِ .",
        "وَ بِالْإِسْنَادِ الْأَوَّلِ فِي الْأُذُنَيْنِ إِذَا قُطِعَتْ إِحْدَاهُمَا فَدِيَتُهَا خَمْسُمِائَةِ دِينَارٍ وَ مَا قُطِعَ مِنْهَا فَبِحِسَابِ ذَلِكَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Sahl Bin Ziyad, from Muhammad Bin Al Hassan Bin Shamoun, from Abdullah Bin Abdul Rahman Al Asamma, from Misma’a, ",
          "Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> has said: ‘Ali<sup>asws</sup> judged regarding an ear lobe, being one-third of the wergild of the ear’.",
          "And by the first chain regarding the two ears when one of them is cut, so its wergild is five hundred Dinars, and whatever is cut from it, it would be by the accounting of that’."
        ]
      }
    }
